#: ../../../release/notes-towncrier.rst:3
msgid "Deprecations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/notes-towncrier.rst:5
msgid ""
"``numpy.char.chararray`` is deprecated. Use an ``ndarray`` with a string or "
"bytes dtype instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/notes-towncrier.rst:7
msgid "(`gh-30605 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/30605>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/notes-towncrier.rst:9
msgid ""
"`numpy.take` now correctly checks if the result can be cast to the provided "
"``out=out`` under the same-kind rule. A ``DeprecationWarning`` is given now "
"when this check fails. Previously, ``take`` incorrectly checked if ``out`` "
"could be cast to the result (the wrong direction). This deprecation also "
"affects ``compress`` and possibly other functions. (Future versions of NumPy "
"may tighten the casting check further.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/notes-towncrier.rst:17
msgid "(`gh-30615 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/30615>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/notes-towncrier.rst:19
msgid ""
"The ``numpy.char.[as]array`` functions are deprecated. Use an ``numpy."
"[as]array`` with a string or bytes dtype instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/notes-towncrier.rst:21
msgid "(`gh-30802 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/30802>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/notes-towncrier.rst:24
msgid "Setting the ``dtype`` attribute is deprecated"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/notes-towncrier.rst:25
msgid ""
"Setting the dtype attribute is now deprecated since mutating an array is "
"unsafe if an array is shared, especially by multiple threads.  As an "
"alternative, you can create a view with a new dtype via `array."
"view(dtype=new_dtype)`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/notes-towncrier.rst:30
msgid "(`gh-29244 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/29244>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/notes-towncrier.rst:33
msgid "Setting the ``shape`` attribute is deprecated"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/notes-towncrier.rst:34
msgid ""
"Setting the shape attribute is now deprecated since mutating an array is "
"unsafe if an array is shared, especially by multiple threads.  As an "
"alternative, you can create a new view via `np.reshape` or `np.ndarray."
"reshape`. For example: ``x = np.arange(15); x = np.reshape(x, (3, 5))``. To "
"ensure no copy is made from the data, one can use ``np.reshape(..., "
"copy=False)``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/notes-towncrier.rst:40
msgid ""
"Directly setting the shape on an array is discouraged, but for cases where "
"it is difficult to work around, e.g., in ``__array_finalize__`` possible "
"with the private method `np.ndarray._set_shape`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/notes-towncrier.rst:43
msgid "(`gh-29536 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/29536>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/notes-towncrier.rst:46
msgid "Deprecation of the ``generic`` unit in `numpy.timedelta64`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/notes-towncrier.rst:48
msgid ""
"Using the ``generic`` unit in `numpy.timedelta64` is now deprecated since "
"this can lead to unexpected behavior such as non-transitive comparisons. "
"(see `gh-28287 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/issues/28287>`__ for details)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/notes-towncrier.rst:52
msgid ""
"As an alternative, please specify an explicit unit such as ``'s'`` (seconds) "
"or ``'D'`` (days) when constructing `numpy.timedelta64`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/notes-towncrier.rst:55
msgid ""
"Due to this change, operations that implicitly rely on the ``generic`` unit "
"are also deprecated. For example::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/notes-towncrier.rst:58
msgid ""
"arr = np.array([1, 2, 3], dtype=\"m8[s]\")\n"
"\n"
"# `1` is implicitly converted to generic timedelta64\n"
"arr + 1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/notes-towncrier.rst:65
msgid "(`gh-29619 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/29619>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/notes-towncrier.rst:68
msgid "Resizing a Numpy array inplace is deprecated"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/notes-towncrier.rst:69
msgid ""
"Resizing a Numpy array inplace is deprecated since mutating an array is "
"unsafe if an array is shared, especially by multiple threads.  As an "
"alternative, you can create a resized array via ``np.resize``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/notes-towncrier.rst:73
msgid "(`gh-30181 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/30181>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/notes-towncrier.rst:76
msgid "``numpy.fix`` is deprecated"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/notes-towncrier.rst:78
msgid ""
"`numpy.fix` is deprecated. Use `numpy.trunc` instead, which is faster and "
"follows the Array API standard. Both functions provide identical "
"functionality: rounding array elements towards zero."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/notes-towncrier.rst:82
msgid "(`gh-30644 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/30644>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/notes-towncrier.rst:85
msgid "``numpy.ma.round_`` is deprecated"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/notes-towncrier.rst:86
msgid ""
"``numpy.ma.round_`` is deprecated. ``numpy.ma.round`` can be used as a "
"replacement."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/notes-towncrier.rst:89
msgid "(`gh-30738 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/30738>`__)"
